The paper deals with algorithms for drawing directed graphs, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. The most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) since the paper presents a new approach to visualize directed graphs and their hierarchies. The paper also involves computational geometry, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.CG (Computational Geometry). Additionally, the paper deals with graph theory and graph drawing, which could place it under cs.GR (Graph Theory). The paper also mentions the reduction of visual complexity, which could suggest that it belongs to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of time complexity, which could place it under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
